    {
      "number": 2,
      "title": "因为...所以... — Because...Therefore...",
      "explanation": "因为 (yīn wèi) means 'because' and 所以 (suǒ yǐ) means 'therefore / so'. They pair together to express cause and effect. Structure: 因为 + Cause, 所以 + Result. Either part can be used alone in context, but together they make the logic very clear.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "因为天气太热，所以我不想吃饭。",
          "pinyin": "Yīn wèi tiān qì tài rè, suǒ yǐ wǒ bù xiǎng chī fàn.",
